The paper deals with the problem of single image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning image priors using both external and internal examples, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sparse coding and epitomic matching, which are common techniques in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR), respectively.
